Lindsay and I have been sharing the good, the bad, and the ugly, for 7 years. Our summers have been a huge part of the foundation for our friendship, relationship and fairytale. Nevertheless, getting engaged in the Hamptons was a dream come true. I’m so glad I pulled off the surprise BUT it wasn’t easy! First and foremost, thank you to The Hubbard Family. I’m so thankful you came all the way from Florida to surprise her. Extremely grateful for all our friends who joined us at Dockers and their support leading up and after. Lindsay had zero idea any of this was happening and seeing these photos says it all. Thank you @imkylecooke @andreadenver for your confidence boost and keeping it a 🤐. Shoutout to @chris_leoni for capturing these precious moments and bringing your extendo lens. And lastly, thank you to @bravotv and our phenomenal production team. I did what I thought was best to pull off this amazing surprise so thank you for your support. What most people don’t realize is that I met with Larry the owner of Dockers at the end of May to ask him personally about hosting a gathering after we got engaged cause it’s one of Lindsay and I’s favorite spots and difficult to film on a Saturday because it’s so busy. Thankfully he obliged and shoutout to Larry and The Dockers team for taking great care of us. From that point began 3 months of planning and trying to keep this a secret. I guess you can say the rest is history. Cant wait to marry my best friend! I love you Lindsay! #SummerHouse
Thank you for all you did to raise us, Mom. It’s no coincidence that MOM upside down is WOW. We love you so much! Happy Mothers Day to ALL the Moms out there 💐🌸🌷

Couple days behind but my first time in the Florida Keys didn’t disappoint. Wonderful trip with The Hubbard Family! Thank you for taking me out on the boat and showing me your 🎣 ways. Still need to work on my sea legs 🥴😂 Love you guys!

Last weekend was😎 Super proud of my friend Dr. Grant Lewis. From a hockey career to graduating dental school it was amazing to witness the big day at University of Minnesota. Super impressive and congrats on the hard work! Hope you enjoyed the extended release surprise🤯 Big things ahead for you. Love you brother 👊🏼

#MentalHealthAwarenessMonth is important to me because of the huge impact therapy has had on my life. I’ve been using Talkspace since 2020 and it’s been instrumental in dealing with the loss of my brother, healing childhood traumas, understanding conflict resolution and expressing my emotions. I’m incredibly passionate about sharing my story in hopes to inspire others to share theirs. Let’s normalize the conversation and show friends and family that you’re always there to listen. Let’s support each other on our mental health journeys and #CelebrateEveryStep. What do you do to celebrate your mental health journey? #Ad #TalkspacePartner

After missing the last couple years I was finally able to play in the annual Joel Cornette Foundation Golf Outing. Phenomenal day top to bottom. @thejordancornette and I have been friends for a few years but really bonded over the last couple with dealing with the loss of a sibling. I truly admire and am inspired by all the work he has done in his brothers memory. It’s impressive to see an incredible group come out to raise money and awareness! I had the absolute pleasure to play with @adamrodriguez and his manager Abe as well as one of my childhood best friends @danduda0 Our squad struggled a bit but we had a doozy playing together. I got to meet a few legends along the way with a big shout out to Coach Bill Self and @jayharrisespn for being so cool. Excited to run it back with you all next year! @joelcornettefoundation

Thank you, Veterans 🇺🇸 October 17th we said goodbye to my Uncle Peter Curtis. He was a decorated Vietnam veteran who served our country with pride and honor. He was my godfather and my mom’s only brother. He was a motivating force in my youth with sports and showing us the ropes around Yale football and hockey. Into my teens he was extremely helpful in my pursuit of tv/film by attending Newhouse at Syracuse University. I’m so grateful for his service but also his love and support. Like many veterans he carried a tremendous burden back home. He suffered a lot in silence and the toll alcohol and mental illness played is a sad reality. Even with the immense burden he spent his adult years bridging the gap between the upper class university and working with the surrounding underprivileged communities. His true mission was supporting local veterans affairs groups and helping those returning home. It was an emotional few days in New Haven but with my Mom,Lou,Debbie and some longtime friends we came to together to give him the proper honoring that he deserved. This also presented an opportunity to finally lay my brothers ashes in a place with my Moms family where we have many memories and roots of the Carmichael/Curtis/Radke family. Uncle Peter, will be missed. Thank you for your service. Curtis, I love you. RIP 💔

Thank you to all the incredible Bravo fans for all your amazing energy, love and support at #BravoCon2023 I met so many kind, warm and generous people who make this whole thing so worth it. We wouldn’t be here without you supporting our shows, brands and coming out to our events! Also a huge thank you to all the folks who worked tirelessly to make it all happen. It’s been a really difficult few months but I am beyond grateful to Bravo and our SH supporters. I extend my heartfelt appreciation for standing by me and providing a continuous source of understanding and love. For those who couldn’t make it, I’m sorry for adding to the fomo 🙏🏼 NA LB coming soon❤️‍🔥
